# Frontend Components

## Anatomy

```tsx
'use client' // only if needed

interface MyComponentProps {
  channelId: string
  onSelect?: (id: string) => void
}

export function MyComponent({ channelId, onSelect }: MyComponentProps) {
  // hooks first
  // derived state next
  // handlers last
  return <div className={cn('...', someCondition && '...')}>...</div>
}
```

- **Named exports only** (no `export default`) for non-route components. Pages and layouts use `default export` as Next.js requires.
- One component per file. File name = component name in `PascalCase.tsx`.
- Hooks at the top, derived values next, handlers last, JSX at the end.

## Composition

- Compose shadcn primitives from `components/ui/`. Don't fork them; if a variant is missing, build a wrapper.
- Co-locate small presentational sub-components in the same file when they're not reused.
- Pull stateful or effect-heavy logic into a hook under `src/hooks/use<Name>.ts`.

## Accessibility

- Every interactive element must be keyboard-navigable (Tab + Enter / Space).
- Use semantic HTML (`button`, `nav`, `main`) over `div` with `onClick`.
- Buttons that wrap icons need `aria-label`.
- `Dialog`, `DropdownMenu`, `Command` (shadcn) are a11y-correct out of the box — prefer them over hand-rolled equivalents.

## Performance

- Memoize only when profiling shows a need. Avoid `useMemo`/`useCallback` cargo-culting.
- Long lists (>50 rows) use `@tanstack/react-virtual`.
- Optimistic updates for any user-initiated mutation that would otherwise feel laggy.

## Testing

- Hook tests in `src/hooks/__tests__/use<Name>.test.ts` with `@testing-library/react`.
- Component tests cover: rendering, primary user interaction, error/empty states.
- API mocked via MSW handlers in `src/test/handlers.ts`.
